        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The ceramic catalytic converter muffler has a drain hole at the mid point along the length of the
                    converter muffler assembly. This drain hole is not an exhaust leak and is necessary to prevent water
                    from entering the ceramic catalytic converter section of the converter muffler.
                </para>
                <para>The soot residue on the back of cab paint is the result of incorrect orientation of the drain
                    hole.
                </para>
                <para>To avoid soot residue on the back of cab paint, the converter muffler drain hole must be
                    repositioned.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, allow the exhaust system sufficient time to cool before performing
                        this Service Procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the clamp at the lower exhaust elbow and converter muffler mounting clamps.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the converter muffler assembly so that the drain hole faces toward the muffler
                    stanchion (Figure 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Retighten the clamps to 27 to 37 Lbf-ft (37 to 50 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
